      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Section 4.1 - Automatic variables, parameters and stack&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;Stack - last in first out implementation&#xA;Call by value says within a function, parameter can be changed but doesn&amp;rsquo;t affect the variable in main. Parameters are &amp;ldquo;isolated&amp;rdquo; within the function. This is accomplished using stack.&#xA;stack frames were used to the variables of function and removed when it is exited.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
