    <item>
      <title>Chapter 5 - Pointers, Arrays</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/personal-site/docs/c/chapter-5-pointers-arrays/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2024 12:18:08 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/personal-site/docs/c/chapter-5-pointers-arrays/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Section 5.1 - Pointers&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;Pointers are where we move &amp;ldquo;below abstraction&amp;rdquo;, where C can replace assembly language.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;expressive-code&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;figure class=&#34;frame not-content&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;figcaption class=&#34;header&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;title&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-c&#34; data-lang=&#34;c&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cp&#34;&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;cpf&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cp&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cp&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;x&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;y&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;%d %p %d&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;//  42  0x16f5b31ec  42&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;int*&lt;/code&gt; integer of type pointer&#xA;&lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;x&lt;/code&gt; to get the address of x&#xA;&lt;code&gt;*px&lt;/code&gt; a look up operator or de-reference operator to get the value in location.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Chapter 6 - Structures</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/personal-site/docs/c/chapter-6-structures/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2024 12:18:19 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/personal-site/docs/c/chapter-6-structures/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Mid Chapter Surprise&#xA;Structures 6.1 - 6.4 - New type&#xA;Data Structures 6.5, 6.6 - Applications of structures&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6.1 Structures&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;A structure is a user defined &lt;code&gt;type&lt;/code&gt; that contain one or more types that can be treated as a unit.&#xA;The elements or variables mentioned in a structure are called &lt;code&gt;members&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;The dot operator allows us to access the members of the structure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Chapter 6.1 - Structures</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/personal-site/docs/c/chapter-6.1-structures/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2024 12:27:38 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/personal-site/docs/c/chapter-6.1-structures/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;chapter-6---structures&#34;&gt;Chapter 6 - Structures&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A structure is a collection of one or more variables, possibly of different types, grouped together under a single name for convenient handling.&#xA;Structures help to organize complicated data, allowing a group of related variables to be treated as a unit instead of separate entities.&#xA;Employee has many attributes, a point is a pair of co ordinates etc.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
